WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.699
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12.882 --> 00:15.885
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

00:17.017 --> 00:20.585
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

00:20.716 --> 00:24.589
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HAVE SOMEBODY ♪

00:24.720 --> 00:27.984
♪ WHEN THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

00:28.115 --> 00:30.726
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

00:30.856 --> 00:33.598
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT

00:36.949 --> 00:38.821
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

00:38.951 --> 00:42.303
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

00:45.480 --> 00:49.353
♪ I'LL BE READY,
I'LL BE READY ♪

00:49.484 --> 00:53.357
♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR,
OH, DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

00:53.488 --> 00:56.447
♪ I'LL BE READY

00:56.578 --> 00:59.711
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

00:59.842 --> 01:02.236
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:20.645 --> 01:22.604
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:22.734 --> 01:26.086
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:29.567 --> 01:33.571
♪ I'LL BE READY,
I'LL BE READY ♪

01:33.702 --> 01:37.488
♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR,
OH, DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

01:37.619 --> 01:40.970
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:41.101 --> 01:43.842
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.973 --> 01:46.976
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:01.947 --> 02:06.822
[ISLAND PERCUSSION MUSIC]

04:44.849 --> 04:46.895
-SHE'S NOT GONNA COME SAILING
UP TO THE BEACH, YOU KNOW.

04:47.025 --> 04:48.418
-YEAH, I KNOW.

04:48.549 --> 04:50.028
I JUST CAN'T WAIT
FOR HER TO COME HOME.

04:50.159 --> 04:51.378
-MITCH: GONNA HAVE TO.

04:52.466 --> 04:54.163
-HEY! HEY, WAIT A MINUTE.

04:54.294 --> 04:55.773
WHAT IS THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

04:55.904 --> 04:58.950
-SHE CALLED ME AND
SAID THAT SHE AND RILEY

04:59.081 --> 05:01.083
WERE STOPPING OFF AT ONE
OF THE CHANNEL ISLANDS

05:01.213 --> 05:03.868
FOR ONE MORE EVENING
OF ROMANTIC ADVENTURE.

05:03.999 --> 05:05.392
-WELL, THAT'S JUST GREAT.

05:05.522 --> 05:07.132
I MEAN, SHE'S
ALREADY BEEN TO FIJI.

05:07.263 --> 05:08.525
SHE'S ALREADY BEEN
TO THE SOLOMONS.

05:08.656 --> 05:09.831
SHE'S BEEN HALFWAY
AROUND THE WORLD,

05:09.961 --> 05:11.746
HOW MUCH MORE ADVENTURE
DOES SHE NEED?

05:11.876 --> 05:15.140
-CAROLINE, I THINK ROMANTIC
IS THE KEYWORD IN THAT PHRASE.

05:15.271 --> 05:17.882
DON'T WORRY, THEY'LL BE
HERE TOMORROW MORNING
AT TEN O'CLOCK.

05:19.928 --> 05:22.713
-YEAH WELL, I GUESS
ONE MORE DAY CAN'T HURT.

05:28.284 --> 05:31.200
-RILEY: [HOOTING] GREAT.

05:34.725 --> 05:39.034
[HOOTING AND LAUGHING]

05:39.164 --> 05:43.995
[AMOROUS ELECTRONIC MUSIC]

05:51.612 --> 05:53.396
YOU KNOW, WE CAN BE
BACK ON TONGA IN A WEEK.

05:53.527 --> 05:55.224
[LAUGHING]

05:59.271 --> 06:00.577
I'M SERIOUS.

06:03.711 --> 06:05.713
-WE'LL TALK, OKAY. PROMISE.

06:11.632 --> 06:12.589
RILEY?

06:12.720 --> 06:13.590
-HUH?

06:13.721 --> 06:14.852
-RILEY, LOOK.

06:14.983 --> 06:16.376
OVER THERE.

06:19.335 --> 06:21.032
-LOOKS LIKE OIL SMOKE.

06:21.163 --> 06:22.599
-WE'D BETTER CHECK IT OUT.

06:31.913 --> 06:34.306
ARE YOU OKAY? WHAT HAPPENED?

06:34.437 --> 06:36.178
-MY BOAT CAUGHT FIRE.

06:36.308 --> 06:38.398
I HAD TO BEACH IT
TO SAVE MY SUPPLIES.

06:38.528 --> 06:40.138
-LOOKS LIKE THAT'S
ALL YOU'RE GONNA SAVE.

06:40.269 --> 06:41.749
-YEAH, I KNOW.

06:41.879 --> 06:43.185
THANK GOODNESS YOU'RE HERE,

06:43.315 --> 06:44.795
I WAS AFRAID I WAS
GONNA BE STRANDED.

06:44.926 --> 06:45.970
-RILEY: ARE YOU OKAY?

06:47.407 --> 06:49.670
-YEAH, YEAH. THANKS.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.760
BY THE WAY, I'M CORAL WHITMAN.

06:52.890 --> 06:53.848
-RILEY FERGUSON.
-CORAL: HI.

06:53.978 --> 06:55.371
-RILEY: STEPHANIE HOLDEN.

06:55.502 --> 06:57.068
-HI.
-HI, STEPHANIE.

06:57.199 --> 06:58.722
-CAN WE GIVE YOU A LIFT?

06:58.853 --> 07:00.550
-YEAH, THAT WOULD BE GREAT.

07:00.681 --> 07:02.204
-WHAT WERE YOU DOING HERE?

07:02.334 --> 07:05.555
-I'M WITH MARINE
ECOLOGY AT UC SAN DIEGO.

07:05.686 --> 07:09.603
I WAS GATHERING SAMPLES
AROUND THE CHANNEL ISLANDS.

07:10.386 --> 07:12.736
I DON'T KNOW, IT JUST, POOF.

07:13.998 --> 07:15.217
WHAT ABOUT YOU GUYS?

07:16.044 --> 07:17.828
-WE WERE JUST DIVING
FOR OUR DINNER.

07:18.873 --> 07:20.396
HEY LOOK, WOULD YOU
LIKE TO JOIN US?

07:21.049 --> 07:22.877
-YEAH. YEAH, OKAY.

07:23.007 --> 07:26.881
THAT WOULD BE GREAT,
I'LL SUPPLY THE FIREWOOD.

07:27.011 --> 07:28.317
-GREAT.

07:29.187 --> 07:30.711
[SIGHING]

07:35.933 --> 07:40.982
[VARIOUS PEOPLE TALKING]
[SINISTER MUSIC]

07:45.595 --> 07:46.640
-HEY!

07:47.597 --> 07:48.380
-HEY!

07:48.511 --> 07:50.078
HE STOLE MY BIKE!

07:54.648 --> 07:56.301
SOMEBODY STOP HIM!

07:56.432 --> 07:57.477
HE STOLE MY BIKE!

07:58.347 --> 08:02.873
[EXCITING GUITAR MUSIC]

08:33.513 --> 08:35.078
-BRAD, ARE YOU OKAY?

08:36.080 --> 08:37.995
HE WENT THAT WAY! GO GET HIM!

08:56.100 --> 08:58.668
[SCREAMING]

09:02.933 --> 09:05.545
-TWO VICTIMS OFF THE SEAL
BEACH PIER, TOWER SIX.

09:06.328 --> 09:11.463
[ACTION-PACKED MUSIC]

10:05.169 --> 10:06.127
-I GOT HIM!

10:19.096 --> 10:22.012
[COUGHING]

10:22.143 --> 10:23.623
-WHERE AM I?

10:23.753 --> 10:24.754
WHO ARE YOU?

10:24.885 --> 10:25.842
-KATHERINE FLEMING.

10:25.973 --> 10:27.757
NO, NO, NO. REST A MINUTE.

10:27.888 --> 10:28.758
-I'M FINE.

10:30.020 --> 10:31.239
MY NAME'S GARNER ELLERBEE.

10:32.240 --> 10:34.634
-PLEASED TO MEET
YOU, OFFICER ELLERBEE.

10:36.331 --> 10:38.028
I'M AFRAID YOUR
ASSAILANT GOT AWAY.

10:39.813 --> 10:40.901
-I'LL FIND HIM.

10:41.031 --> 10:42.729
AND, CALL ME GARNER. [GROANS]

10:43.338 --> 10:45.775
-WHOA, YOU'D BETTER TAKE IT
EASY FOR THE REST OF THE DAY.

10:46.820 --> 10:48.560
LET ME TAKE YOU
UP TO MY TOWER.

10:58.614 --> 11:03.967
[HAPPY HUMMING]

11:07.449 --> 11:08.842
-AH, WHAT A BABY.

11:08.972 --> 11:10.104
-GARNER: MITCH, BUDDY.

11:11.192 --> 11:13.629
-AREN'T YOU A LITTLE OLD TO
BE JOINING JUNIOR LIFEGUARDS?

11:13.760 --> 11:15.718
-AH, NEVER TOO OLD, MITCH.

11:16.676 --> 11:18.155
SAY, BUDDY, WHAT CAN YOU
TELL ME ABOUT A LIFEGUARD

11:18.286 --> 11:19.809
NAMED KATHERINE FLEMING?

11:20.680 --> 11:23.160
-ALMOST NOTHING, EXCEPT THAT
SHE'S 26 YEARS OLD, SINGLE,

11:23.291 --> 11:27.208
A CERTIFIED PARAMEDIC, GORGEOUS
AND IN INCREDIBLE SHAPE.

11:27.338 --> 11:28.775
WHY?

11:28.905 --> 11:30.864
-OH, NOTHING, JUST GLAD
TO SEE ANOTHER LIFEGUARD

11:30.994 --> 11:32.474
WITH A PERMANENT TAN.

11:32.604 --> 11:35.259
-OH, THIS IS PURELY AN
EQUAL OPPORTUNITY THING.

11:35.390 --> 11:36.478
-HEH, CUTE.

11:37.784 --> 11:39.829
-AND, ALL THINGS BEING EQUAL.

11:39.960 --> 11:42.223
-I'D LIKE THE OPPORTUNITY
TO SHOW HER HOW EXCITING

11:42.353 --> 11:43.485
THE BEACH CAN BE AT NIGHT.

11:43.615 --> 11:44.399
SHE DATING ANYBODY?

11:44.529 --> 11:45.835
-NOT THAT I KNOW OF.

11:46.793 --> 11:48.229
BUT THERE IS ONE THING.

11:48.359 --> 11:49.534
-WHAT'S THAT?

11:49.665 --> 11:52.712
-SHE'S DEAF IN HER RIGHT EAR.

11:53.800 --> 11:55.192
HAPPENED DURING A RESCUE.

11:55.932 --> 11:58.021
WE ONLY TALK INTO HER LEFT EAR.

11:58.674 --> 11:59.849
-YEAH, RIGHT.

11:59.980 --> 12:01.721
-NO, LEFT.
-RIGHT. LEFT.

12:01.851 --> 12:02.765
-RIGHT.

12:03.853 --> 12:04.767
-RIGHT?

12:04.898 --> 12:08.118
-[CHUCKLING] NO, LEFT.

12:08.249 --> 12:09.467
-LEFT?
-RIGHT.

12:10.991 --> 12:12.209
-GOT IT.
-GOOD.

12:12.340 --> 12:13.820
-OKAY. [SIGHS]

12:13.950 --> 12:15.038
-ALL RIGHT.

12:16.561 --> 12:17.780
THE DIE HAS BEEN CAST.

12:19.303 --> 12:21.044
-CORAL: THAT WAS
DELICIOUS, THANK YOU.

12:22.959 --> 12:23.917
-STEPHANIE: YOU'RE WELCOME.

12:25.527 --> 12:27.094
-MAKES ME KIND OF SAD, THOUGH.

12:28.312 --> 12:29.705
OUT OF THE THREE
CHANNEL ISLANDS,

12:29.836 --> 12:31.228
THIS IS THE ONLY ONE
THAT'S NOT POLLUTED.

12:32.708 --> 12:33.927
-YEAH, IT IS SAD.

12:34.057 --> 12:34.928
-IT'S CRIMINAL.

12:35.058 --> 12:36.320
-YOU GOT THAT RIGHT.

12:37.452 --> 12:40.324
THE OCEAN IS DEFINITELY
A LADY UNDER ATTACK.

12:40.847 --> 12:43.240
-THE OCEAN'S ALWAYS
BEEN MALE TO ME.

12:44.198 --> 12:46.374
A MAN'S POWER, EMBRACE.

12:48.115 --> 12:49.377
HIS MORTALITY.

12:49.507 --> 12:50.813
-MORTALITY?

12:52.293 --> 12:54.469
-I WAS IN ALASKA
AFTER THE EXXON VALDEZ.

12:56.645 --> 13:00.692
HAVE YOU EVER HELD A
SEAGULL COVERED WITH OIL?

13:00.823 --> 13:03.434
FELT ITS HEART
POUNDING WITH FEAR.

13:03.565 --> 13:06.133
-WELL, IT IS EASY TO FORGET
HOW FRAGILE OUR WORLD IS.

13:06.263 --> 13:09.397
-NO ONE LISTENS,
STEPHANIE. NO ONE CARES.

13:10.006 --> 13:11.878
-THERE ARE A LOT OF PEOPLE
OUT THERE LIKE YOU, CORAL.

13:12.661 --> 13:14.054
-YEAH, THEN THEY'RE ASLEEP.

13:14.184 --> 13:16.491
AND THEY'LL NEED A
DESPERATE WAKE-UP CALL.

13:20.625 --> 13:22.932
[LAUGHING] JUST LISTEN
TO ME, WOULD YOU.

13:23.063 --> 13:27.023
I'M SORRY, I AM JUST
COMPLETELY MAXED OUT.

13:27.154 --> 13:31.419
-YOU KNOW, I THINK A LITTLE
REST WOULD DO US ALL SOME GOOD.

13:32.028 --> 13:33.813
YOU CAN STAY WITH THE
FIRE IF YOU WANT, CORAL.

13:33.943 --> 13:35.945
STEPHANIE AND I CAN
BED DOWN ON THE BOAT.

13:36.076 --> 13:38.687
-NO, THAT'S RIDICULOUS.
YOU CAN STAY HERE.

13:38.818 --> 13:40.471
IT'S WAY MORE ROMANTIC.

13:40.602 --> 13:41.603
-I'LL JUST GET MY THINGS
AND FIND A SPOT DOWN THE BEACH.

13:41.733 --> 13:43.170
-NO, CORAL, YOU CAN'T.

13:43.300 --> 13:44.606
-DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.

13:44.736 --> 13:45.912
YOU LOVEBIRDS HAVE
A SPECIAL EVENING.

13:46.042 --> 13:47.174
GOOD NIGHT.

13:56.836 --> 14:02.145
[DEVIOUS MUSIC]

14:13.504 --> 14:14.462
-KATHERINE.

14:14.984 --> 14:16.290
-HI, GARNER.

14:16.420 --> 14:17.552
-BYE, GARNER.

14:20.294 --> 14:22.687
-IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME
SINCE SOMEONE SAVED MY LIFE.

14:23.340 --> 14:25.777
-SO NOW YOU BELONG
TO ME, RIGHT?

14:25.908 --> 14:28.780
-AH, NO, NO.

14:30.608 --> 14:34.047
-I WAS HOPING FOR SOMETHING
A LITTLE MORE ORIGINAL.

14:38.225 --> 14:39.226
-HOW ABOUT THIS?

14:41.054 --> 14:42.925
I KNOW A PLACE WHERE
THE STEAKS ARE SO FINE,

14:43.056 --> 14:45.145
THE COWS LINE UP TO
JUMP ON THE GRILL.

14:46.494 --> 14:47.712
-SCOUT'S HONOR?

14:47.843 --> 14:50.019
-WELL, I NEVER WAS SCOUT, BABY,

14:50.150 --> 14:52.282
BUT I AM ALWAYS PREPARED.

14:53.501 --> 14:56.939
-UM, I DON'T
ORDINARILY EAT MEAT,

14:57.070 --> 15:00.377
BUT I MIGHT MAKE AN
EXCEPTION TONIGHT.

15:01.552 --> 15:04.251
I'LL MEET YOU IN THE PARKING
LOT IN ABOUT FIVE MINUTES?

15:04.381 --> 15:05.600
OKAY?

15:07.776 --> 15:08.646
-I'LL BE THERE.

15:08.777 --> 15:11.345
[NERVOUS LAUGHTER]

15:18.700 --> 15:19.744
-KATHERINE: MITCH.

15:20.615 --> 15:21.746
-MITCH: HEY, KATHERINE.

15:23.270 --> 15:25.402
-CAN I ASK YOU ABOUT GARNER?

15:25.533 --> 15:27.143
-MITCH: YEAH, WHAT
DO YOU NEED TO KNOW?

15:27.274 --> 15:30.712
-KATHERINE: WELL, HE'S
AWFULLY NICE BUT HE'S A LITTLE--

15:30.842 --> 15:32.714
-A LITTLE ODD, PERHAPS?

15:32.844 --> 15:34.934
-[SIGHS] I HATE
TO SAY IT, BUT YES.

15:36.413 --> 15:37.632
-STEP OVER HERE.

15:41.244 --> 15:42.289
IT'S HIS HEARING.

15:42.419 --> 15:44.030
-HIS HEARING?

15:44.160 --> 15:48.730
-YEAH, IT HAPPENED FOUR
YEARS AGO, A KIDNAP SITUATION,

15:48.860 --> 15:52.255
GARNER WRENCHED A GUN AWAY
FROM THE VICTIM'S HEAD,

15:52.386 --> 15:53.778
NEARLY TOOK THE BLAST HIMSELF.

15:53.909 --> 15:55.215
BAM!

15:55.345 --> 15:57.478
WENT OFF RIGHT BY HIS RIGHT EAR.

15:57.608 --> 15:59.001
-MY GOODNESS.
-YEAH.

15:59.828 --> 16:02.744
YOU KNOW, COPS LIKE
GARNER, THEY COME ALONG

16:02.874 --> 16:04.093
ONCE IN A GENERATION.

16:04.702 --> 16:06.748
THE CITY GAVE HIM
THIS BEACH, YOU KNOW.

16:06.878 --> 16:09.620
THE PEACEFUL DUTY, THE
SUN, SAND AND THE SURF

16:09.751 --> 16:11.013
IN HUMBLE GRATITUDE.

16:11.144 --> 16:13.102
-OH, MITCH, WHAT CAN I DO?

16:13.233 --> 16:16.062
-WELL, I THINK YOU
SHOULD DO WHAT WE DO.

16:16.192 --> 16:18.978
WE TALK ONLY INTO HIS LEFT EAR.

16:22.416 --> 16:23.721
-I WON'T FORGET.

16:23.852 --> 16:25.549
-MITCH: OKAY.
ALL RIGHT, TAKE CARE.

16:25.680 --> 16:26.681
-KATHERINE: OKAY.

16:27.551 --> 16:29.292
-I LOVE MATCHMAKING.

16:29.858 --> 16:32.208
[LAUGHING]

16:37.083 --> 16:38.736
-OKAY, SHORT STUFF.

16:39.868 --> 16:42.218
A LIFELONG HONEYMOON EVERY NIGHT

16:42.784 --> 16:44.916
SPENT UNDER A
DIFFERENT EXOTIC SKY.

16:45.482 --> 16:46.918
-I DON'T KNOW, RILEY.

16:47.702 --> 16:49.660
I DON'T KNOW IF
I'M BUILT FOR THAT.

16:49.791 --> 16:51.445
I NEED WORK.

16:51.575 --> 16:53.795
-I HAVE SURVEY CONTRACTS
ALL OVER THE SOUTH PACIFIC.

16:55.057 --> 16:57.451
-THAT'S YOUR WORK.
I MEAN MY WORK.

16:58.756 --> 17:00.758
I JUST LOVE THE
ACTION ON THE BEACH.

17:05.372 --> 17:06.721
-AND I LOVE YOU.

17:08.288 --> 17:10.159
LOOK, I KNOW YOU HAVE
QUESTIONS ABOUT US,

17:11.160 --> 17:12.335
BUT LOVE ISN'T JUST TWO PEOPLE

17:12.465 --> 17:13.815
LOOKING AT EACH OTHER'S STUFF.

17:14.816 --> 17:17.036
IT'S TWO PEOPLE LOOKING
IN THE SAME DIRECTION.

17:19.299 --> 17:21.692
I MEAN, THERE'S A WHOLE
WORLD OUT THERE WAITING,

17:22.476 --> 17:24.042
AND IT'S WAITING JUST FOR US.

17:25.348 --> 17:26.654
-RILEY, I--
-HEY, HEY.

17:27.785 --> 17:30.136
I'M JUST ASKING
YOU TO CONSIDER IT.

17:39.754 --> 17:41.147
WILL YOU?

17:44.715 --> 17:49.633
[ROMANTIC GUITAR MUSIC]

18:14.267 --> 18:16.269
[YAWNING]

18:39.118 --> 18:40.206
-CORAL!

18:41.337 --> 18:42.730
THAT'S OUR BOAT!

18:43.470 --> 18:44.688
CORAL!

19:14.370 --> 19:20.071
[TENSE MUSIC]

19:42.268 --> 19:43.269
-CORAL: STEPHANIE.

19:44.531 --> 19:46.663
-CORAL, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

19:46.794 --> 19:48.143
-YOU SAID
YOU'D GIVE ME A LIFT,

19:48.274 --> 19:50.450
SO I THOUGHT I'D
MOVE MY SUPPLIES.

19:50.580 --> 19:52.060
I DIDN'T WANT TO WAKE YOU.

19:53.888 --> 19:55.759
I WAS JUST GONNA TAKE
HER CLOSER TO CAMPSITE.

19:55.890 --> 19:57.152
PICK YOU BOTH UP.

19:59.850 --> 20:01.156
HONEST, STEPHANIE.

20:09.556 --> 20:11.253
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY!

20:12.428 --> 20:13.951
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

20:14.082 --> 20:16.040
-I JUST WANT TO SEE
WHAT'S INSIDE THESE CASES.

20:16.171 --> 20:18.347
-THEY'RE JUST MY SUPPLIES.

20:18.478 --> 20:20.349
-WELL, THEN YOU WON'T
MIND IF I TAKE A LOOK.

20:24.788 --> 20:26.790
-NO. OF COURSE NOT.

20:29.140 --> 20:30.403
WHY SHOULD I MIND?

20:34.624 --> 20:40.239
[GRUNTING AND GROANING]

20:41.805 --> 20:47.158
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

20:58.779 --> 21:01.608
[GAGGING]

21:08.092 --> 21:12.619
[GROANING]

21:26.285 --> 21:29.679
[PANTING]

21:46.783 --> 21:48.219
-STEPHANIE!

21:51.092 --> 21:52.180
-ANY WORD FROM STEPHANIE?

21:52.311 --> 21:53.660
-NO, NOT A WORD.

21:53.790 --> 21:55.531
-[SIGHS] SHE'S TWO HOURS LATE.

21:55.662 --> 21:58.708
I MEAN, I SET MY
WATCH BY THIS WOMAN.

22:00.101 --> 22:01.885
SOMETHING'S WRONG.

22:30.697 --> 22:33.787
[TENSE MUSIC]

22:33.917 --> 22:35.571
EXPLOSIVES?

22:47.801 --> 22:49.716
-GRANCIA, I'M
GOING ON MY WORKOUT.

22:59.900 --> 23:00.814
HI.

23:00.944 --> 23:01.902
-GARNER: HEY.

23:02.032 --> 23:03.643
-I WAS JUST THINKING ABOUT YOU.

23:03.773 --> 23:05.384
-THINKING WHAT EXACTLY?

23:06.036 --> 23:08.735
-THAT MAYBE YOU
NEED TO WORKOUT MORE.

23:08.865 --> 23:09.866
-EXCUSE ME?

23:10.693 --> 23:12.565
-YOU'RE VERY GOOD LOOKING.

23:12.695 --> 23:15.698
BUT YOU DON'T WANT
TO GET TOO SOFT.

23:15.829 --> 23:18.179
-SOFT? MY LADY, I'LL HAVE
YOU KNOW THIS BODY CAN LIFT

23:18.309 --> 23:20.311
MORE WEIGHT THAN ANY
MUSCLE MAN YOU CAN DIG UP.

23:23.053 --> 23:24.403
-GREAT UPPER BODY.

23:24.533 --> 23:25.926
BUT WHAT ABOUT THIS?

23:26.056 --> 23:27.144
-OW! HEY, HEY, HEY!
-WHAT'S THE MATTER?

23:27.275 --> 23:28.798
YOU CAN'T GET AWAY?

23:28.929 --> 23:30.496
OH, I DIDN'T MEAN
TO EMBARRASS YOU.

23:30.626 --> 23:31.888
-I'M NOT EMBARRASSED.

23:32.019 --> 23:34.151
UNDER THIS LIES SOLID MUSCLE.

23:34.282 --> 23:35.979
-THEN WHY DO YOU COVER IT UP?

23:36.850 --> 23:37.981
-BECAUSE I LIKE TO EAT.

23:38.678 --> 23:40.070
IT'S ONE OF LIFE'S
GREAT PLEASURES.

23:42.551 --> 23:44.031
-IT'S NOT THE BEST.

23:45.772 --> 23:46.816
-WHAT IS THE BEST?

23:47.861 --> 23:50.385
-IF YOU GET IN SHAPE,
MAYBE YOU'LL FIND OUT.

23:51.647 --> 23:52.779
-HOW LONG'S YOUR BREAK?

23:53.606 --> 23:54.650
-AN HOUR.

23:56.260 --> 23:57.392
-COME WITH ME.

23:57.523 --> 23:58.567
-WHERE ARE WE GOING?

23:59.568 --> 24:03.920
-TO GET OUT OF THESE CLOTHES
AND EXPERIENCE REAL PLEASURE.

24:04.791 --> 24:06.401
[LAUGHING]

24:06.532 --> 24:12.363
[UPBEAT GUITAR MUSIC]

24:41.044 --> 24:44.265
-♪ OH RUN AWAY WITH ME

24:44.395 --> 24:48.530
♪ LET'S GET LOST IN A FANTASY

24:48.661 --> 24:53.056
♪ SATISFY OUR WILDEST DREAMS

24:53.927 --> 24:56.059
♪ IN A SWEET RELEASE

24:57.060 --> 25:01.543
♪ YOUR EYES LIGHT A FIRE
DEEP INSIDE OF ME ♪

25:01.674 --> 25:06.156
♪ I'M FILLED WITH DESIRE
AND YOUR LOVE'S WHAT I NEED ♪

25:06.287 --> 25:08.419
♪ I'M CRAVING YOU

25:08.550 --> 25:11.248
♪ GOT ME IN THE MOOD

25:11.379 --> 25:14.164
♪ YEAH WE'RE LIVING IN A FANTASY

25:14.295 --> 25:18.299
♪ EVERY DAY I WANT YOU HERE WITH ME
YEAH WE'RE LIVING IN OUR WILDEST DREAMS ♪

25:18.429 --> 25:20.431
♪ GOT ME IN THE MOOD

25:20.562 --> 25:22.999
♪ CUZ I REALLY WANNA LOSE CONTROL

25:23.130 --> 25:25.219
♪ AND I REALLY WANT YOUR BODY AND SOUL

25:25.349 --> 25:30.746
♪ IT'S THE ONLY THING I'VE EVER KNOWN
GOT ME IN THE MOOD ♪

25:30.877 --> 25:35.359
♪ THAT YOU GOT ME
GOT ME IN THE MOOD ♪

25:49.896 --> 25:51.593
-ANY WORD FROM STEPHANIE YET?

25:51.724 --> 25:52.812
-STILL NO WORD.

25:53.377 --> 25:57.686
-[SIGHS] THIS IS
BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS,

25:57.817 --> 25:59.775
I'M TRYING TO REACH
LIEUTENANT STEPHANIE HOLDEN

25:59.906 --> 26:01.037
ON THE WHITE LADY.

26:01.168 --> 26:03.126
STEPHANIE? DO YOU READ ME?

26:03.953 --> 26:05.041
-MITCH.

26:05.868 --> 26:06.913
MITCH?

26:08.001 --> 26:09.219
WHAT ARE YOU DOING!

26:11.918 --> 26:12.919
-WHAT I HAVE TO DO.

26:15.312 --> 26:16.749
PEOPLE ARE EXPECTING US.

26:17.837 --> 26:19.926
-THEY'RE GONNA BE LOOKING
FOR RILEY AND ME, YOU KNOW.

26:20.056 --> 26:21.318
-THAT DOESN'T MATTER.

26:22.319 --> 26:24.495
-SEE? THEY'RE
LOOKING FOR US NOW.

26:27.673 --> 26:29.109
-MITCH!

26:32.460 --> 26:33.896
-WHAT WAS THAT?

26:34.854 --> 26:35.855
-STEPHANIE?

26:36.943 --> 26:38.422
STEPHANIE, DO YOU READ ME?

26:39.685 --> 26:41.469
I WANT A SCARAB READY
IN FIVE MINUTES.

26:41.600 --> 26:44.080
-BAYWATCH TO SCARAB ONE,
COME IN PLEASE.

26:44.211 --> 26:46.605
-NO ONE'S GONNA FIND YOU.

26:47.388 --> 26:49.433
AND NO ONE'S GONNA
FIND THIS BOAT.

26:50.043 --> 26:54.264
ALL THEY'RE GONNA FIND IS TINY
LITTLE ASHES SOAKED IN OIL.

26:59.400 --> 27:03.056
-LOOK, CORAL. UNTIE ME, OKAY?

27:03.186 --> 27:04.231
WE CAN TALK ABOUT THIS.

27:04.361 --> 27:05.798
-THERE'S NOTHING TO TALK ABOUT.

27:08.191 --> 27:09.540
-YOU'RE MAKING A BOMB
WITH ENOUGH PLASTIQUE

27:09.671 --> 27:10.846
TO BLOW UP A WHOLE CITY BLOCK,

27:10.977 --> 27:11.847
AND THERE'S NOTHING
TO TALK ABOUT?

27:11.978 --> 27:14.110
-I AM THROUGH TALKING.

27:15.242 --> 27:16.852
TALKING GETS YOU NOWHERE.

27:16.983 --> 27:18.158
-AND NEITHER DOES VIOLENCE.

27:18.288 --> 27:20.029
-VIOLENCE GETS
PEOPLE'S ATTENTION.

27:21.248 --> 27:22.945
IT'S THE EXCLAMATION POINT
AT THE END OF THE SENTENCE.

27:23.076 --> 27:25.861
IT GIVES THE WORDS
YOU SAY IMPACT.

27:27.515 --> 27:29.299
NOW THEY'RE GONNA
HAVE TO LISTEN.

27:29.430 --> 27:33.739
-LOOK, CORAL, I'M SURE THE
MOTIVES YOU HAVE ARE JUST, OKAY?

27:34.783 --> 27:39.092
I KNOW
THE SYSTEM IS FRUSTRATING,
BUT THIS IS NOT THE ANSWER.

27:39.745 --> 27:43.618
-THE SYSTEM.
-WHAT SYSTEM, STEPHANIE?

27:44.488 --> 27:47.753
WHAT ABOUT THE ECOSYSTEM?
WHAT ABOUT THE SOLAR SYSTEM?

27:47.883 --> 27:49.798
ARE WE GONNA WAIT
UNTIL THEY DESTROY THAT

27:49.929 --> 27:51.365
BEFORE WE TAKE ACTION?

27:53.976 --> 27:55.412
-WHAT ACTION, CORAL?

27:56.370 --> 27:57.719
WHAT ARE YOU PLANNING TO DO?

28:03.638 --> 28:05.292
-SHOW THE GREEDY
POLLUTERS OF THE WORLD

28:05.422 --> 28:08.034
WHAT ONE DETERMINED
WOMAN CAN DO.

28:08.164 --> 28:11.254
AND YOU OR NO ONE ELSE
IS GOING TO STOP ME.

28:19.785 --> 28:23.702
[EXCITING MUSIC]

28:29.838 --> 28:31.971
-HERE! OVER HERE!

28:38.499 --> 28:41.807
SHE SAID SHE WAS A
MARINE ECOLOGIST HERE
GATHERING SAMPLES.

28:42.721 --> 28:44.331
BUT I FOUND THAT IN THE BOAT.

28:46.115 --> 28:48.857
-YOU SURE STEPHANIE DIDN'T
GO WITH HER VOLUNTARILY?

28:49.553 --> 28:51.468
-AND LEAVE ME HERE? NO WAY.

28:52.208 --> 28:54.428
NOW LOOK, CHECK THIS
OUT, I FOUND THIS MAP.

28:54.558 --> 28:57.170
NOW SHE CIRCLED THE AREA
OFF THE COAST OF SAN PEDRO.

28:57.300 --> 28:58.345
WHAT'S IN THERE?

29:00.477 --> 29:03.872
-THAT'S THE LARGEST OIL
PLATFORM IN SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA.

29:06.788 --> 29:10.270
-KATHERINE: BABY, I
AM GONNA PUMP YOU UP.

29:10.400 --> 29:12.533
-WHOA, WHOA. WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

29:12.663 --> 29:15.188
-HEY, YOU HAVE GOT
TO CHANGE YOUR DIET.

29:15.318 --> 29:17.016
CUT OUT THE FAT
AND THE RED MEAT.

29:17.146 --> 29:19.148
-I'M IN LOVE WITH
A FITNESS MANIAC.

29:21.585 --> 29:23.283
-I AM NOT A MANIAC.

29:24.153 --> 29:25.589
-WAIT A MINUTE, YOU HEARD THAT?

29:25.720 --> 29:27.504
-OF COURSE I HEARD THAT.

29:27.635 --> 29:31.073
-BUT I-- YOU'RE NOT
DEAF IN YOUR LEFT EAR?

29:31.204 --> 29:33.336
-DEAF? ME? NO!

29:33.467 --> 29:34.816
MITCH TOLD ME YOU WERE DEAF.

29:34.947 --> 29:36.035
-MITCH?

29:37.340 --> 29:40.517
OH BOY, I'M GONNA
GET HIM FOR THIS ONE.

29:48.569 --> 29:50.919
-I'LL NEVER FORGIVE MYSELF
IF ANYTHING HAPPENS TO HER.

29:51.050 --> 29:53.182
-STEPHANIE CAN TAKE
CARE OF HERSELF.

29:53.313 --> 29:55.228
-YEAH, I KNOW, SHE DOESN'T
NEED ANYONE, THAT'S HER PROBLEM.

29:56.707 --> 29:58.666
-TOOK YOU TWO MONTHS
AT SEA TO FIND THAT OUT?

29:59.536 --> 30:00.450
-YEAH.

30:01.364 --> 30:03.889
SHE SAID SHE LOVES
ME, BUT DOESN'T KNOW

30:04.019 --> 30:05.673
IF SHE WANTS TO SPEND THE
REST OF HER LIFE WITH ME.

30:16.553 --> 30:22.298
[EXCITING MUSIC]

30:26.825 --> 30:28.304
-CORAL: A MILLION
GALLONS OF OIL SUCKED OUT

30:28.435 --> 30:29.740
OF THE OCEAN FLOOR EVERYDAY.

30:30.393 --> 30:31.830
IT'S GONNA LIGHT UP THE SKY.

30:33.048 --> 30:35.181
-AND DESTROY EVERYTHING
THAT YOU WANT TO PROTECT.

30:35.964 --> 30:38.227
-IT'S A SACRIFICE FOR
THE GREATER GOOD.

30:43.537 --> 30:45.756
-WHAT ABOUT ME, AM I
BEING SACRIFICED TOO?

30:47.933 --> 30:49.325
-I'M SORRY, STEPHANIE.

30:50.022 --> 30:51.937
BUT EVERY WAR HAS
ITS CASUALTIES.

30:52.067 --> 30:53.590
-YOU'LL DIE TOO.

30:54.200 --> 30:56.463
-NO, I'LL HAVE LEFT ON
THE DINGHY BEFORE YOU CRASH

30:56.593 --> 30:57.638
INTO THE PLATFORM.

30:59.553 --> 31:01.076
-STEPHANIE: SOMEONE
HAS TO SAIL THE BOAT.

31:03.122 --> 31:06.125
-WELL, UNLIKE PEOPLE,
NATURE IS DEPENDABLE.

31:06.255 --> 31:08.736
SEE, I HAVE POSITIONED US SO
THAT WHEN I RAISE THE SAIL,

31:08.867 --> 31:11.217
THE WIND AND THE CURRENT
WILL JUST TAKE YOU

31:11.347 --> 31:12.653
STRAIGHT INTO THE PLATFORM.

31:13.436 --> 31:15.525
SHOULD TAKE ABOUT
THREE SHORT MINUTES.

31:16.396 --> 31:18.050
AND THIS WILL GIVE
ME ENOUGH TIME TO DO

31:18.180 --> 31:19.051
WHAT I HAVE LEFT TO DO.

31:20.748 --> 31:22.576
-LOOK, CORAL, DON'T DO THIS.

31:24.926 --> 31:27.102
-I WAS WILLING TO
SACRIFICE MY OWN LIFE.

31:27.798 --> 31:29.670
AND THEN FATE DESTROYED MY
BOAT AND BROUGHT ME TO YOURS,

31:29.800 --> 31:31.454
SO DON'T BLAME ME.

31:32.281 --> 31:33.195
THIS IS YOUR FATE.

31:34.066 --> 31:35.850
AND THE FATE OF EVERYONE
ON THAT OIL RIG.

31:39.723 --> 31:45.512
[SERIOUS MUSIC]

32:11.277 --> 32:15.977
[TENSE ELECTRONIC MUSIC]

32:16.108 --> 32:19.372
[PANTING]

32:27.336 --> 32:31.950
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

32:54.363 --> 32:55.364
-THERE'S CORAL!

32:56.061 --> 32:57.279
-YOU SEE STEPHANIE?

32:58.150 --> 32:59.020
-NO.

33:35.230 --> 33:36.710
-ALL RIGHT, TAKE THE WHEEL.

33:36.840 --> 33:37.841
-I'LL GO, I KNOW THE BOAT.

33:37.972 --> 33:39.756
-NO, I KNOW EXPLOSIVES.

33:43.760 --> 33:44.718
-I'LL GO AFTER CORAL.

33:44.848 --> 33:45.762
-NOT YET.

33:51.159 --> 33:55.511
[PANTING]

34:20.667 --> 34:21.929
-MITCH: STEPH?

34:22.060 --> 34:23.061
-MITCH.

34:24.192 --> 34:25.628
-YOU ALL RIGHT?
- YES.

34:25.759 --> 34:27.500
-LOOK, SHE'S RIGGED
EXPLOSIVES TO A TIMER.

34:27.630 --> 34:29.067
AND WE'VE GOT TO GET
THE BOAT OFF COURSE

34:29.197 --> 34:30.764
BEFORE IT RUNS INTO THE OIL RIG.

34:30.893 --> 34:31.982
-NO, SHE'S JAMMED THE
WHEEL AND LOCKED THE BOAT

34:32.112 --> 34:34.463
ON AUTO-PILOT ON COURSE.

34:34.594 --> 34:36.074
I'M GONNA HAVE TO
DISARM THE BOMB.

34:36.204 --> 34:38.163
LOOK, RILEY'S ON THE SCARAB.

34:38.293 --> 34:39.206
GO ON, GET OUT OF HERE.

34:39.338 --> 34:40.687
-NO, I'M STAYING WITH YOU.

34:40.817 --> 34:42.254
-LOOK, THERE'S NOTHING
YOU CAN DO HERE. GO ON.

34:42.384 --> 34:44.125
-I WATCHED HER ACTIVATE
THE BOMB, I CAN HELP.

34:46.606 --> 34:51.567
[TENSE MUSIC]

35:08.976 --> 35:11.935
-DO ME A FAVOR,
THERE'S A FLASHLIGHT
IN THE POUCH, GRAB IT.

35:13.154 --> 35:14.155
AND POINT IN THAT
HOLE RIGHT THERE.

35:16.026 --> 35:17.332
-HOW BAD IS IT?

35:18.159 --> 35:19.378
-IT'S A NIGHTMARE.

35:19.508 --> 35:21.119
THERE'S ENOUGH
PLASTIQUE IN THERE

35:21.249 --> 35:22.598
TO BRING DOWN A BATTLESHIP.

35:23.643 --> 35:26.036
AND THIS IS THE BIGGEST
DETONATOR, I HAVE SEEN

35:26.167 --> 35:28.038
SINCE I WAS A NAVY SEAL.

35:28.169 --> 35:29.823
-CAN YOU JUST REMOVE
THE WHOLE BOMB?

35:31.172 --> 35:32.391
-I'LL FIND OUT.

35:33.218 --> 35:35.655
[BEEPING]

35:37.222 --> 35:38.179
-STEPHANIE: WHAT IS THAT?

35:40.225 --> 35:42.662
-SHE'S GOT A MAGNETIC TRIGGER
ATTACHED TO THE METAL PLATE.

35:44.054 --> 35:46.274
THERE'S NO WAY THE
TWO CAN BE SEPARATED.

35:48.624 --> 35:53.760
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

36:00.767 --> 36:02.247
-STEPHANIE: SO
WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

36:02.377 --> 36:05.380
-GO UP ON DECK, SEE IF
YOU CAN CHANGE COURSE

36:05.511 --> 36:07.165
AT LEAST TO HEAD US
AWAY FROM THE RIG.

36:08.209 --> 36:11.647
I'M GONNA TRY AND DETACH THE
DETONATOR FROM THE EXPLOSIVES.

36:21.744 --> 36:22.832
-STEPH!

36:23.616 --> 36:26.532
STEPH! YOU'RE HEADING
RIGHT INTO THE RIG.

36:36.063 --> 36:37.282
-RILEY, TURN US!

36:37.412 --> 36:40.110
-WHAT?
-TURN US, PUSH US OFF COURSE!

36:41.199 --> 36:42.287
-HANG ON!

36:50.033 --> 36:54.603
[DRAMATIC ORCHESTRAL MUSIC]

37:34.077 --> 37:37.516
[INTENSE MUSIC]

37:48.701 --> 37:49.658
-ONE MORE.

37:52.705 --> 37:54.837
[SIGHING] OH GOD.

37:54.968 --> 37:59.277
[TRIUMPHANT MUSIC]

38:00.278 --> 38:02.280
I'M COMING OUT
WITH THE DETONATOR.

38:04.586 --> 38:05.935
-STEPHANIE: MITCH, HURRY!

38:10.157 --> 38:11.811
[GRUNTING]

38:23.953 --> 38:24.911
LOOK.

38:25.738 --> 38:27.566
-MITCH: AH, SHE WANTS TO
CLEAN UP HAZARDOUS WASTE?

38:27.696 --> 38:28.915
LET'S START WITH HER.

38:38.620 --> 38:40.143
-STEPHANIE: IT'S
ALL OVER, CORAL.

38:40.274 --> 38:41.536
IT'S OVER.

38:46.498 --> 38:51.416
[PLEASANT PIANO MUSIC]

38:52.852 --> 38:57.900
[APPLAUSE]

39:10.304 --> 39:12.175
-CAROLINE: OH, I'VE
MISSED YOU SO MUCH.

39:12.306 --> 39:13.481
-STEPHANIE: I MISSED YOU TOO.

39:16.223 --> 39:17.659
I DIDN'T KNOW HOW MUCH
I MISSED BEING HERE

39:17.790 --> 39:19.748
UNTIL I THOUGHT I MIGHT
NEVER MAKE IT BACK.

39:21.097 --> 39:22.751
-WELL, YOU'D BETTER
NOT GO AWAY AGAIN.

39:22.882 --> 39:24.100
NOT ANY TIME SOON.

39:29.279 --> 39:31.020
-I'LL BE BACK.

39:31.151 --> 39:33.327
-WELL, WHERE ARE YOU GOING?
-IN A MINUTE.

39:44.599 --> 39:45.470
HEY.

39:46.079 --> 39:47.733
-RILEY: HEY.

39:47.863 --> 39:49.038
-STEPHANIE: IT'S NOT LIKE
YOU TO BE OFF BY YOURSELF.

39:50.213 --> 39:52.346
-JUST WATCHING HOW
MUCH EVERYONE LOVES YOU.

39:58.526 --> 40:00.528
-I LOVE YOU, YOU
KNOW THAT, DON'T YOU?

40:02.878 --> 40:04.314
YOU COULD STAY HERE, YOU KNOW.

40:04.924 --> 40:06.186
BE A PART OF MY WORLD.

40:10.451 --> 40:11.539
-WOULDN'T WORK.

40:13.846 --> 40:15.500
-LOVE ISN'T TWO PEOPLE
LOOKING AT EACH OTHER.

40:15.630 --> 40:18.981
IT'S TWO PEOPLE LOOKING
IN THE SAME DIRECTION.

40:23.333 --> 40:25.118
YOU WON'T STAY AWAY
FOREVER, WILL YOU?

40:25.988 --> 40:27.250
-HOW COULD I?

40:29.252 --> 40:34.214
[PEACEFUL GUITAR MUSIC]

40:48.620 --> 40:50.752
-STEPHANIE TOLD RILEY
THAT SHE'S STAYING HERE.

40:50.883 --> 40:51.666
-PARDON ME?

40:52.885 --> 40:54.277
-I SAID THAT
STEPHANIE TOLD RILEY

40:54.408 --> 40:55.801
THAT SHE'S GONNA STAY HERE.

40:57.150 --> 40:58.238
-WHAT?

40:59.544 --> 41:04.462
-STEPHANIE TOLD RILEY THAT
SHE IS GOING TO STAY HERE.

41:04.592 --> 41:06.681
-WHY ARE WE WHISPERING?

41:08.857 --> 41:12.470
-BECAUSE KATHERINE
AND GARNER SAID THAT--

41:12.600 --> 41:14.776
-KATHERINE AND GARNER WHAT?

41:14.907 --> 41:16.778
-CAROLINE: KATHERINE
AND GARNER TOLD ME

41:16.909 --> 41:19.041
THAT YOUR EARS
WERE HYPERSENSITIVE
SINCE THE EXPLOSION,

41:19.172 --> 41:21.914
AND YOU COULDN'T
TOLERATE LOUD NOISES.

41:22.044 --> 41:22.958
[LAUGHING]

41:23.089 --> 41:24.264
-TOUCHE.

41:25.178 --> 41:26.440
-IT'S NOT OVER YET.

41:26.571 --> 41:27.702
-WHAT? WHAT?

41:27.833 --> 41:28.834
-WHAT'D YOU SAY?

41:28.964 --> 41:32.707
[LAUGHING]

41:33.578 --> 41:35.101
-MITCH: OH, GOD.

41:37.146 --> 41:40.846
[END THEME PLAYING]
